race.comment: SELENA'S CHANCE (1) clocked a new course and distance PB last time, finishing a 1.5 lengths second behind Roar Of Thunder in 18.97. Rates a top chance if runs up to latest. TIME FOR TEA (2) has missed the placings at her last couple but was in the money three back when second (22.66) at Ballarat in a T3 Grade 6. With a good start should be able to take advantage of the low draw. Can improve sharply here. PERFECT LIAM (3) flew the lids with a fast split and led throughout with a 2.5 lengths win over 425m at Bendigo (24.12). Can make it two on the bounce. PA KETTLE (8) cannot be underestimated.
